05026nam a22007095i 9783110746679DE-B159720220629043637.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220629t20222022gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2021941797  a97831107466797 a10.1515/97831107466792doi  a(DE-B1597)579666  a(OCoLC)1294426107  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aREL0510002bisacsh1 aJunker-Kenny, Maureen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut15a"The Bold Arcs of Salvation History" :bFaith and Reason in Jürgen Habermas’s Reconstruction of the Roots of European Thinking /cMaureen Junker-Kenny. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (XVIII, 288 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tAbbreviations -- tIntroduction -- t1 Recent Philosophical Debates on the Hermeneutics of Past Events and Their Relevance for Biblical Research -- t2 Reconstructing the Position of Paul in Early Christianity -- t3 Tracing the Origins of the Doctrine of Christ -- t4 Assessing the Pauline Strand: Exegetical, Methodological and Theological Disputes and Conclusions -- t5 The Patristic Era as Setting the Course for Relating Religion to Reason -- t6 The Origins of Modernity in the Late Middle Ages -- t7 “Faith” and “Knowledge” after the Copernican Turn in Kant’s Critiques of Reason -- t8 Post-Kantian Theories of Language – Pacemakers for the Paradigm Change from Subject Philosophy to Linguistic Interaction -- t9 Reappraising the Counterparts: Secular Reason as the Default Position, Religion as “Other”? -- tBibliography -- tPerson Index -- tSubject Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book offers the first in-depth treatment in English language of Habermas’s long-awaited work on religion, Auch eine Geschichte der Philosophie, published in 2019. Charting the contingent origins and turning points of occidental thinking through to the current "postmetaphysical" stage, the two volumes provide striking insights into the intellectual streams and conflicts in which core components of modern self-understanding have been forged. The encounter of Greek metaphysics with biblical monotheism has led to a theology of history as salvation, expanding in bold arcs from Adam’s Fall to Christ and the Last Judgement. The reconstruction of key turns in the relationship between faith and knowledge ends, however, with locating the uniqueness of religion in "ritual" and defining reason as inherently secular. The book exposes the sources and trajectories, analysed by Habermas with great erudition, to different assessments in biblical studies, theology, and philosophy of subjectivity. Apart from Paul and Augustine, key lines of continuity are identified in the Gospels, early patristic theology, Duns Scotus and Schleiermacher that retain the internal connection of faith to autonomous freedom.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aRELIGION / Philosophy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022 Englishz978311099454408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107467300 cprintz978311074629740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074667940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110746679423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110746679/original  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-09